  # Agent config rules from .claude/skills/review/SKILL.md
  - id: agent_config_no_large_binary_files
    type: fail_to_pass
    origin: agent_config
    description: No large / binary files in git check implemented as per SKILL.md rule
    source:
      file: .claude/skills/review/SKILL.md
      lines: "226-228"
      commit: cf5fb461472203d56bb0c169a61d194dd97fc2f2
      rule: "Binary blobs (JARs, archives, compiled artifacts, datasets >1 MB, fat dependency bundles) must never be committed. They permanently bloat the repository for every clone and cannot be removed without history rewriting."

rubric:
  - rule: "Add comments explaining invariants and rationale for complex logic, not just narrating what the code does. Every byte committed to git is cloned forever — bulk stat via xargs is preferred over fork-per-file for performance."
    source:
      path: ".claude/skills/review/SKILL.md"
      lines: "226-230"
      commit: "cf5fb461472203d56bb0c169a61d194dd97fc2f2"

  - rule: "Scripts should detect platform differences (GNU vs BSD tools) explicitly rather than failing per-file. Use feature detection, not version checks."
    source:
      path: ".claude/skills/review/SKILL.md"
      lines: "141-150"
      commit: "cf5fb461472203d56bb0c169a61d194dd97fc2f2"

  - rule: "Follow existing code style in the file being modified. Match surrounding brace style, indentation, and quoting patterns."
    source:
      path: ".claude/CLAUDE.md"
      lines: "1-50"
      commit: "cf5fb461472203d56bb0c169a61d194dd97fc2f2"
